[101]NPR's 'Trump's Terms' podcast examines President Trump's plans for his
second term

   [102]November 25, 2024  Host Scott Detrow to curate NPR's reporting on
   Donald Trump's plans for his second-term

   [103]NPR's Books We Love guide returns in 2024.

   NPR's Books We Love guide returns in 2024. Chelsea Conrad/NPR hide
   caption
   toggle caption
   Chelsea Conrad/NPR

[104]NPR's Books We Love returns for its 12th year

   [105]November 25, 2024  The 2024 edition of the guide offers over 350
   new reading recommendations.

[106]NPR and stations in Appalachia and the Mid-South launch new regional
newsroom

   [107]November 19, 2024  NPR and NPR Member organizations in Appalachia
   and the Mid-South have launched a collaboration aimed at strengthening
   local news coverage and bringing more stories from this region to the
   rest of the country.

[108]NPR launches new series 'Seeking Common Ground: Conversations Across the
Divide'

   [109]November 19, 2024  NPR will feature a week of stories and
   conversations taking a closer look at how people across the country are
   finding common ground on important issues despite their differences.

[110]NPR Board Elects Sarah Morris as Member Director

   [111]November 15, 2024  NPR welcomes the election of Sarah Morris to
   the NPR Board of Directors.

[112]Make NPR your 2024 election night news source

   [113]October 28, 2024  You can follow along on your local Member
   station broadcast, online at NPR.org, through the NPR App, or on your
   smart speaker. We’ll also share updates on social media at
   Facebook.com/nprpolitics and Instagram/nprpolitics, with recaps on the
   NPR Politics Podcast.
